parameters: It's a morning that's no different from usual.

I ended up failing to install the antenna, so today I
thought I'd go a little further and climbed up the hill
behind.
Hikaru
It's hot, isn't it...

When I first came to this island, it was quite cool as long
as I avoided the midday hours, but before I knew it, it
had become completely summer.

I took a deep breath while walking along the forest path
where the traces of people were starting to fade.

Still, I feel like being on this island where I can breathe
in the clear air is better than being in the
suffocating city.
I should be able to leave before summer vacation ends.
I don't know.
By the way, the road is quite narrow.

When I try to climb such a narrow road, I feel like I've
become Bokusoku.
Will I become Bokusoku or Deng Ai?

I don't want to be remembered as a successful
mountaineer.
Janjan aichiki chikibanban.
Ai chiki chiki chan chan.
It feels like being in a sauna with the steam.

Summer time is short, isn't it? Are you enjoying your
summer?
Rushing, rushing on the Ferris wheel!
...No, let's stop thinking like this.
Will I lose to summer? My mind is a mess.
Oh.
Oh...
There is no road.

The road leading to Asahara was submerged in water,
perhaps due to the previous heavy rain.

Well, you know... Asahara is usually close to wetlands, so
it's possible for something like this to happen...

Anyway, since it's impossible to move forward any further, the
moment they tried to go back...
A wild boar appeared!
The wild boar used a reckless charge!
Hikaru
Why!?
If our eyes meet, it's a sudden charge showdown!
Hikaru
Uoooh!
I avoided the charging wild boar and reflexively rolled.
That crazy wild boar is attacking people!
No, I take back what I said about it being crazy!
Don't come!

I avoided the charging wild boar and rolled again,
wondering if I'm not tired.
Stop, my life is already at zero!
The wild boar passed by me and went on for a while...
With a bang, it became quiet.
inoshishi (1)
Did it...?
Ah, this is a death flag.
inoshishi (2)
inoshishi (3)

When the dust cleared, the figure that could be seen within
was a wild boar digging into the ground.

It's a fierce charge to the point where you can hear a
tremendous sound, but it doesn't seem to be causing any
damage at all.
Rather, they're angry at me for getting involved!

It seems like there's no other choice but to run with all
my might until their anger subsides...!
